.TH "TEMPORAL.INSTANT.FROM" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.Instant.from \- Temporal.Instant.from()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Temporal.Instant.from()\f[B]\f[R] static method creates a
new \f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R] object from another
\f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R] object, or an RFC 9557 string.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
Temporal.Instant.from(info)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]info\f[R]
One of the following:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
A \f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R] instance, which creates a copy of the
instance.
.IP \(bu 2
An RFC 9557 string containing a date, time, and time zone offset.
The time zone name is ignored; only the offset is used.
.RE
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R] object representing the instant in
time specified by \f[CR]info\f[R].
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]TypeError\f[R]
Thrown if \f[CR]info\f[R] is not a \f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R] instance
or a string.
.TP
\f[B]RangeError\f[R]
Thrown in one of the following cases:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
The string is not a valid RFC 9557 string.
.IP \(bu 2
The info is not in the representable range, which is ±10\(ha8 days, or
about ±273,972.6 years, from the Unix epoch.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Creating an instant from a string
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] instant = Temporal.Instant.from(\(dq1970\-01\-01T00Z\(dq);
console.log(instant.toString()); \f[I]// 1970\-01\-01T00:00:00Z\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] instant2 = Temporal.Instant.from(\(dq1970\-01\-01T00+08:00\(dq);
console.log(instant2.toString()); \f[I]// 1969\-12\-31T16:00:00Z\f[R]

\f[I]// America/New_York is UTC\-5 in January 1970, not UTC+8\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] instant3 = Temporal.Instant.from(\(dq1970\-01\-01T00+08:00[America/New_York]\(dq);
console.log(instant3.toString()); \f[I]// 1969\-12\-31T16:00:00Z; the time zone name is ignored\f[R]
.EE
.SS Creating an instant from another instant
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] instant = Temporal.Instant.from(\(dq1970\-01\-01T00Z\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] instant2 = Temporal.Instant.from(instant);
console.log(instant2.toString()); \f[I]// 1970\-01\-01T00:00:00Z\f[R]
.EE
